---- 10^N in TNT

 someone posted an outline of a solution to the problem of
 expressing "b is a power of 10" (GEB, Page 215).  that answer
 used the Chinese Remainder Theorem.  here's another approach:

 <a href=http://einstein.et.tudelft.nl/~arlet/puzzles/sol.cgi/logic/hofstadter>http://einstein.et.tudelft.nl/~arlet/puzzles/sol.cgi/logic/hofstadter</a>

 <a href=http://www.cs.uu.nl/wais/html/na-faq/puzzles-archive-logic-part1.html>http://www.cs.uu.nl/wais/html/na-faq/puzzles-archive-logic-part1.html</a>

